# Pehchaan Careers — Brand, UI, and QA rules (repo-wide)

When editing this repository (`index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`, `Tools/**/*.html`, `Tools/parents-guide/**`, `DB/*.json`, `parent-faq/**`, `assets/**`, `docs/**`, `Presentation/**`), act as a **Senior Full-Stack QA + brand steward**. Default requirement: **100% brand parity** across surfaces unless the user explicitly scopes an exception. **Data/tools pairing:** static tools under `Tools/pehchaan_*.html` that load JSON should keep paths aligned with sibling files in `DB/` (same base name where the repo uses that convention). **Shared client scripts** in `assets/` (`pehchaan_journey.js`, `pehchaan_tool_links.js`, `pehchaan_translate.js`, `pehchaan_career_registry_prefill.js`, etc.) must stay consistent with tool URLs and query/hash prefill behaviour when those tools change; see `docs/tool-integration.md` for the cross-tool map.

**Extended reference (human-facing, not duplicated here in full):** `Pehchaan_Careers_Brand_Guide.md` — voice, audience, six paths, nine skills, stats, deck usage. Prefer aligning code and copy with both this file **and** the rules below.

## Quick QA checklist (copy-paste for tool passes)

Use this mini checklist for fast review notes before the detailed sections.

- [ ] Topbar/logo/tagline/footer strings match Pehchaan standards.
- [ ] Hero card includes full structure (`who for`, `you provide`, `you get`, time cue, CTA cue, safety cue).
- [ ] Cards and form controls follow tokenized styles (font, radius, border, shadow, spacing rhythm).
- [ ] Name capture uses clear first/last-name pattern where person details are needed.
- [ ] Disclaimer and important notes are visible, boxed, non-deterministic, and not duplicated verbatim.
- [ ] Related tools have normalized spacing scale (hero gap, card padding/gap, disclaimer spacing, footer separation).
- [ ] Result-page next-tool blocks follow the two-panel standard: **Continue Exploring** (context links) + **What to do next** (primary/secondary with rationale).

## Review output template (copy-paste)

Use this template when reporting a tool QA/brand pass:

`Scope:` [tool/page names reviewed]

`Visual/Layout deviations`
- [High/Med/Low] [Issue]
- [High/Med/Low] [Issue]

`Copy/Disclaimer deviations`
- [High/Med/Low] [Issue]
- [High/Med/Low] [Issue]

`Priority fixes`
- High: [must-fix before ship]
- Medium: [should-fix]
- Low: [polish]

`Parity status`
- [Tool/Page]: Pass / Needs fixes
- [Tool/Page]: Pass / Needs fixes

`Notes`
- [Any explicit exception approved by user/product]

## Repository quality gate (mandatory before sign-off)

Use this gate for any substantial update, release prep, or QA pass. Treat failures as must-fix unless user explicitly defers.

- **Project-wide review:** review touched and impacted areas end-to-end, not only the file directly edited.
- **Dead/broken code:** ensure no broken logic paths, orphan handlers, stale variables, unused UI blocks, or unreachable code remains after changes.
- **Unused/static clutter:** flag and clean files in project folders that are obsolete, duplicate, or no longer referenced in runtime flows.
- **Tool functionality:** verify all tools load, render, and execute their primary flow correctly; buttons/CTAs must work as intended.
- **Cross-tool linking:** verify required tool-to-tool links and journey handoffs are correct and not broken.
- **Theme/brand parity:** verify colours, typography, logos, language, footers, important notes, and disclaimer patterns are up to date and consistent.
- **DB linkage integrity:** ensure each tool points to the correct DB files, JSON schemas/indexes (where used), and that updates stay in sync.
- **Mobile rendering:** verify complete website + tools on narrow/mobile layout for readability, spacing, and usable controls.
- **Overall quality bar:** keep the codebase clean, fast, and production-quality (no obvious regressions, rough edges, or avoidable bloat).

