## 3. Two shells: marketing site vs tool pages

### A) Marketing homepage — `index.html` + `styles.css`
- **Header:** `.site-header` — dark gradient bar, **light** logo in `.brand`, pill nav, **Poppins** from Google Fonts. **Do not** paste the tool **topbar** (back arrow + small square mark) here unless product requests a unified shell.
- **Nav labels (current):** Home, Career Reality, Tools, Pathways, Contact Us — preserve casing and anchors (`#home`, `#reality`, etc.) when editing.
- **Footer structure:** Three zones — **brand column** (logo link to `#home`, Hindi tagline, short about blurb), **link columns** (Navigate, Cities We Serve, Connect), **footer-bottom** copyright. **Connect block:** `buddy@pehchaancareers.in`, `hello.pehchaan@gmail.com`, `pehchaancareers.in`, Instagram `https://instagram.com/pehchaancareers`, YouTube `https://youtube.com/@PehchaanCareers`. Keep `rel="noreferrer"` on external links.
- **Copyright line pattern:** `©` + year + `Pehchaan Careers.` + short honesty line — update year via existing script pattern in `script.js` / `#footer-year`, do not hardcode stale years in multiple places.

### B) Standalone tools — `Tools/pehchaan_*.html` (and exam roadmap HTML)
- **Topbar (required):** Back control **`←`** linking to **`../index.html`** (or correct relative home for nested tools), `aria-label` like “Back to Pehchaan Careers home”, **brand row** = 40×40 mark + **Pehchaan Careers** (`font-weight` 700, ~15px, colour **`#085041`**) + second line **`Your identity. Your path.`** (~11px, **`#64748B`**). Match spacing from **`Tools/pehchaan_plan_b_strategy_builder.html`** (consistent across steps).
- **Back button:** ~40×40, rounded 12px, `background: rgba(29,158,117,.12)` (or `.14`), text **`#085041`**, hover state slightly stronger green tint — copy from reference tool.

### C) `parent-faq` (Next.js) and `Tools/parents-guide` (export)
- Reuse **`PehchaanToolChrome.tsx`** patterns for topbar/hero/footer strings and colours.
- **`PEHCHAAN_HOME_RELATIVE`:** `/index.html` — do not change to a broken relative `../` from deployed paths without checking both dev and static export.

---

## 4. Tool footer (three-part, center-aligned)

Every tool screen that uses the standard tool footer must include **all** of the following, **in order**, with the same **meaning** and **contact order** as reference tools:

1. **Motto line:** `Aapki pehchaan, aapki raah.` — visually distinct (e.g. semibold, teal `#1D9E75` or class `.brand-tagline`).
2. **Attribution line:** `This tool is brought to you by` + **`Pehchaan Careers`** wrapped in `<strong>` (strong colour **`#085041`**).
3. **Contact line:** `hello.pehchaan@gmail.com · buddy@pehchaancareers.in · pehchaancareers.in` — use middle dots with normal spaces as in `Tools/pehchaan_stream_advisor.html` / `PehchaanToolChrome.tsx`.

**Rules**
- **Do not** omit line 3 on wizard/pivot steps.
- **Do not** change email strings, domain, or separator style between tools.
- Wrapper: top border `1px solid` teal-light `#E1F5EE`, centered text, muted grey `#64748B` at ~11px for lines 2–3 unless matching an existing class block exactly.

When refactoring, **diff footers** across all modified HTML/TSX files before merge.

